[According to the Chief Medical Officer of Liberia, Dr. Bernice Dahn, an estimated 515 000 Liberians are suffering from mental illness as a result of the prolonged civil war and the Ebola epidemic ranging from victims of rape and other forms of sexual violence and those affected by substance abuse, starting from mild to severe personality disorder]

